      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(streaming): opt-in persistProgress mode for tool+commentary lines",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `streaming.progress.persistProgress` config flag (opt-in, default false)\n- When enabled, completed tool+commentary progress lines are frozen and prepended above the final answer instead of being wiped\n- Shared infra change in `channel-streaming.ts` and `progress-draft-compositor.ts` benefits all channels\n- Telegram: respects 4096 char limit, truncates oldest lines, `---` divider between progress and answer\n\n## Motivation\n\nThe P2 commentary draft system (#87072) is transient by design -- progress lines are wiped when the answer starts streaming. This PR adds an opt-in mode to persist the chronological tool+commentary record in the final message.\n\nBuilds on #87072 (merged) and pairs with #89834 (Claude CLI commentary events).\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `src/config/types.base.ts` -- `persistProgress` on shared `ChannelStreamingProgressConfig`\n- `src/config/zod-schema.providers-core.ts` -- schema entry\n- `src/channels/streaming.ts` -- `resolveChannelStreamingProgressPersist` + persist mode in `mergeChannelProgressDraftLine`\n- `src/channels/progress-draft-compositor.ts` -- frozen line tracking + `formatFrozenProgressText(charBudget)`\n- `extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.ts` -- prepend frozen progress to final answer\n- `extensions/telegram/src/config-ui-hints.ts` -- UI hint\n- `extensions/discord/src/config-ui-hints.ts` -- UI hint\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] 3 tests in `channel-streaming.test.ts` (resolver, persist stacking, default unchanged)\n- [x] 4 tests in `progress-draft-compositor.test.ts` (freeze on suppress, no freeze when off, char budget, empty when off)\n- [x] Existing tests pass\n",
        "branch": "feat/persist-tool-commentary-progress",
